value.0: The Silver Dragons serve and protect the people, acting as the first line of defense against would-be villains and criminals.
This is a settlement guard insignia for the guard templates.

This water carries the fresh, resinous scent of pine and forest. When poured over the heated sauna stones, it bursts into hissing vapor, filling the room with a warm, fragrant fog. The moist heat clings to skin and breath alike, beading on lashes and hair, easing tension from tired muscles as the woodland scent settles into the air like a deep, cleansing breath.

This water carries the soft, calming scent of lavender. When poured over the heated sauna stones, it blooms into a gentle cloud of steam, the warm, fragrant mist settling against skin and breath alike. The moist heat wraps around weary muscles, easing tension and quieting the mind as the soothing aroma drifts through the room, inviting rest and slow, steady breaths.

This water carries the crisp, invigorating scent of eucalyptus. When poured over the heated sauna stones, it rises in a rush of warm steam, the sharp, clean aroma cutting through the heat. The moist fog opens the breath, clears the senses, and washes over skin in a bracing wave, leaving lungs refreshed and the body tingling with renewed energy.

This water carries the delicate, romantic scent of rose. When poured over the heated sauna stones, it unfurls into a soft, fragrant steam, the warm mist settling gently over skin and breath. The moist heat relaxes weary muscles while the floral aroma lingers in the air, soothing the senses and wrapping the room in a tender, comforting calm.
The tabletop of this magnificently built round table has finely inlaid patterns using several types of wood, making it a prized furnishing for anyone with an eye for decor.

A beautiful statue stands in quiet dedication to the naiad Tae'vyn, who once guarded the Feylake of Kohlingen. The elusive fey is captured in her signature attire: a flowing loincloth and matching top, fashioned to resemble drifting seaweed, as if woven from living strands of the lake itself. The sculpted forms ripple with an illusion of motion, giving the impression that she might at any moment step free of stone and return to the water she holds so dear.
